{"lemma":"مُقْعَد","slug":"مُقْعَد","root":"ق.ع.د","root_slug":"ق-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ع-د","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُقْعَد","root":"قعد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35969","n35970","n35974"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seat"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the verb قَعَدَ (qaʕada, “to sit down”)."},"ipa":["/maq.ʕad/","/miq.ʕad/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35969","headword_ar":"مَقْعَدٌ","root":"qEd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of sitting; a sitting-place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoEadapN","text_ar":"مَقْعَدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, K:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqaAEidu","text_ar":"مَقَاعِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sittingplaces of people in the markets &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa min~iY maqoEada AlqaAbilapi","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنِّى مَقْعَدَ القَابِلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is, with respect to me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the sitting-place of the midwife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in nearness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is sticking close to me, before me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S:) denoting nearness of station. (Sb, L.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoqidN","text_ar":"مَعْقِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakuwA maqaAEidahumo","text_ar":"تَرَكُوا مَقَاعِدَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They left their places of abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A time of sitting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF.) ―         -b4-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaqoEadapu","text_ar":"المَقْعَدَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The anus"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as is shown in the S and Msb, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAsuwr","text_ar":"بَاسُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., and so in modern Arabic; and app. also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the posteriors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon which one sits]: syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAflapu","text_ar":"السَّافلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["L","K","Msb","Sb","S"]},{"entry_id":"n35970","headword_ar":"مُقْعَدٌ","root":"qEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having a disease which constrains him to remain sitting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crippled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deprived of the power of motion, by a disease in his body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though the disease constrained him to remain sitting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deprived of the power to stand, by protracted disease; as though constrained to remain sitting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected by a disease in his body depriving him of the power to walk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lame"},{"kind":"text","text":"man (S, L:) also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaminN","text_ar":"زَمِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) accord. to the physicians,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqoEadN","text_ar":"مُقْعَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaminN","text_ar":"زَمِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn.; [see the second explanation above, which is that here indicated;] but some make a distinction, and say that the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the limbs contracted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a protracted disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) [which is app. one of the two significations assigned to the former word in the Msb:] accord. to some, it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quEaAdN","text_ar":"قُعَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying a disease which affects camels in their haunches: (L:) [and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqoEadN","text_ar":"مُقْعَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is applied to] a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having this disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqoEadu Aln~asabi","text_ar":"مُقْعَدُ النَّسَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mqEd AlA^asobaAbi","text_ar":"مقعد الاَسْبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of short lineage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqoEadu AlHasabi","text_ar":"مُقْعَدُ الحَسَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quEodudN","text_ar":"قُعْدُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqoEadu AlA^anofi","text_ar":"مُقْعَدُ الاَنْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having wide nostrils:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having wide and short nostrils."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoYN muqoEadN","text_ar":"ثَدْىٌ مُقْعَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A breast that is swelling, prominent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protuberant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that fills the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and has not yet become folding."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biy^orN muqoEadapN","text_ar":"بِيْرٌ مُقْعَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well that is partly dug, and then left before the water has come into it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musohabapN","text_ar":"مُسْهَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqoEadaAtN","text_ar":"مُقْعَدَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Young birds of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTFA","text_ar":"قَطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before they rise"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to fly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Frogs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Mgh","L","Msb","S","A"]},{"entry_id":"n35974","headword_ar":"مُقَعِّدٌ","root":"qEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqoEidN","text_ar":"مُقْعِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}